<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AFC G-05908 - All FE 300 Bus Models Built Between March 1, 2004 and April 5, 2005 with Allison Automatic
        Transmissions May Develop a Transmission Fluid Leak in the Jumper Hose Between the Radiator In-Tank Transmission
        Cooler and the Transmission Air to Oil Cooler
    </stitle>
    <afc id="afc05908">
        <afcnum>G-05908</afcnum>
        <afcdate>July, 2005</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subject>All FE 300 Bus Models Built Between March 1, 2004 and April 5, 2005 with Allison Automatic
            Transmissions May Develop a Transmission Fluid Leak in the Jumper Hose Between the Radiator In-Tank
            Transmission Cooler and the Transmission Air to Oil Cooler
        </subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>FE 300
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>03/01/2004</startdate>
                        <enddate>04/05/2005</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>
                    <exhotlnk document="../afcs/AFC05908.pdf" bookname="AFC">Print ready (PDF file) copy of the AFC
                        letter
                    </exhotlnk>
                </para>
                <para>The transmission cooler jumper hose straight flare fitting was over-crimped by the supplier
                    causing radial cracks in the interior layer of the hose. With time the transmission fluid may
                    penetrate the hose layers and cause degradation.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
