        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="4">
            <title>service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury from hot transmission fluid, allow the vehicle to cool sufficiently
                        before performing this Service Procedure.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The transmission cooler jumper hose fittings are visible through the access openings in
                    the front bumper (Figure 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f059081" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/G059082.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Arrows Indicate Access Openings</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. See Figure 3 for Enlarged View</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. See Figure 4 for Enlarged View</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position a suitable clean container below the jumper hose flare fitting on the passenger
                    entry side of the bus. Disconnect the jumper flare hose fitting (Figure 2, Item 1) and allow the
                    transmission fluid to drain into the container.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the p-clip (Figure 2, Item 2), disconnect the remaining hose flare fitting and
                    remove the jumper hose.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new jumper hose and reinstall the p-clip following the previous Steps in
                    reverse order. Tighten the jumper hose flare fittings to 52 to 57 Lbf-ft (70 to 77 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f059082" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0590801.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Transmission Cooler Jumper Hose Location and Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Crimped Hose Fittings</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. P-Clip</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Coolant Jumper Hose</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f059083" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g059083b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="376px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. View Through Bumper Opening on Driver Side, Disconnect Flare Fitting (Arrow)
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f059084" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g059084b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="376px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. View Through Bumper Opening on Passenger Side, Disconnect Straight Flare Fitting
                    (Arrow)
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refill the transmission to the correct level with the appropriate transmission fluid.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
